<BR>
And to the person that says I am wrong about Charisma affecting prices. Charsima does affect your price on certain items but it is not the only thing that affects it. Your faction with the merchants do, and the price varies from each merchant. If you dont believe me try selling and buying from a merchant that is &quot;apprehensive&quot; to you, and then try it from a merchant that is amiable or above, you will see a price difference. And in case you didnt know you dont see a major change in the prices of &quot;low cost&quot; items as much as you would a &quot;high cost&quot; item. In other words dont put alot of charisma gear on and then test it buy trying to buy muffins. Try to buy a Steel breastplate or some rubies and see the price difference. I have bought many gems for my warrior and ranger friends while they are doing their quests because I can save them almost 20pp just buy having a higher base charisma.<BR>
